rComments: For someone who loudly and often proclaims her class is an inclusive and safe space, this class provides zero accessibility and is very restrictive. Amy is eurocentric SJW to the max, interrupts students passive aggressive and super awkward to listen to. She is enthusiastic but overshares, def takes a certain type of student to enjoy her class
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Prof AC is very enthusiastic and makes class discussion really enjoyable. People complain that she can call you out in class but its just to make you participate, if you have nothing to say its not a big deal. I came late to every class and she never said anything. Provides extra credit and marking is fair as long as you follow the outline given
Hard for second year class but learning a lot. She will call on you if she doesnt know you.

Prof Clanfield has a way of discussing the most difficult of topics in such a way that any in the class can engage. She is fair, friendly, and smart, but don't be late, and don't talk out of turn. Fair in her grading and her comments are extremely helpful.

Really enjoyed the course (religion and sexuality). Clanfield encourages debate and discussion while still keeping everyone respectful (since sexuality can be a touchy topic). Class hadn't been taught for a while so no precedent set, and she did a really good job of setting the class up. Be on time, she's easily distracted and will call you out.

Pros: Midterm questions given beforehand, take home exam, don't learn much Cons: Rude to students, don't learn much, so many readings (100+ pages a week) Don't show up even 1 minute late or prepare to be chastised in front of the class. Get ready for threatening letters aimed at the whole class about plagiarism. Attendance is mandatory.
